"{\"uid\": \"rappler.com-sports-zeng-zhiying-exits-paris-olympics-2024-but-not-table-tennis\", \"text\": \"  SUMMARY  This is AI generated summarization, which may have errors. For context, always refer to the full article.  SHOT. Table tennis player Zeng Zhiying of Chile in action against Mariana Sahakian of Lebanon during their women's singles preliminary round match in the 2024 Paris Olympics.  Kim Hong-Ji/REUTERS  PARIS, France - Zeng\\u00a0Zhiying, the 58-year-old who made her Olympic debut in Paris representing Chile, ended her Games journey after losing in the preliminary round on Saturday, July 27.  In a tight game full of long rallies,\\u00a0Zeng\\u00a0was beaten 4-1 by 46-year-old Lebanese player Mariana Sahakian.  \\\"I definitely wanted to win, but I think I still performed at my own level. I tried to disrupt my opponent, but she was basically unaffected,\\\" said\\u00a0Zeng.  While her Olympics lasted less than 24 hours,\\u00a0Zeng\\u00a0said she plans to remain active in the sport, which she returned to during the coronavirus lockdown after a decades-long break following a professional career in China.  Zeng, who was part of China's national team over 40 years ago, enjoyed a reunion as\\u00a0she reconnected\\u00a0with a former teammate, 61-year-old Ni Xialian, who is representing Luxembourg.  Zeng, who has lived in Chile for decades, acknowledges this might be her only shot at the Olympics, but she plans to remain active in tournaments.  \\\"Competing again in the Olympics after another four years should be very difficult,\\\" said\\u00a0Zeng. \\\"As long as my body is not injured, I will still play. Even if I can not play at this level, I can still play at the Masters level.\\\"  She was cheered by a packed house at the South Paris Arena, which included her husband and two sons, who had travelled from Chile. She plans to spend more time with them exploring Paris.  \\\"But I do not feel very sad, because this is sport. My husband, my sons, everyone I love and care about were there shouting my name. I feel so content,\\\"\\u00a0Zeng\\u00a0said.- Rappler.com  How does this make you feel?  follow us          \"}"